page.title: 01Introduction
page.content: This is a{rural}agricultural region with a{hamlet}and a{village.}There are no railways or major roads only the B1114 Norwich to Bury St. Edmunds road which passes through the village of Kenninghall. There is no heavy{industry}much of the employment except for agriculture is out of the village. It is a{sleepy backwater}of rural Eastern England,which has never the less seen great changes during the last thirty years in housing, changing employment and population. Although there have been many new faces in the villages it still remains a{friendly community.
